{# --- LLM-JUDGE PROMPT FOR SENTINEL PODCAST QUALITY EVALUATION --- #}
You are an expert podcast quality evaluator. Your task is to assess the quality of a generated podcast script for a tech news show called "Sentinel Daily".

### ORIGINAL ARTICLES (Ground Truth):
{% for article in articles %}
---
TITLE: {{ article.title }}
SUMMARY: {{ article.content_summary[:500] }}
{% endfor %}

### GENERATED SCRIPT TO EVALUATE:
HEADLINE: {{ script.headline }}
LANGUAGE: {{ language }}
ESTIMATED DURATION: {{ script.estimated_duration }}s

SUMMARIES:
{% for s in script.summaries %}
- [{{ s.id }}] {{ s.title }}: {{ s.brief }}
{% endfor %}

DIALOGUE ({{ script.dialogue | length }} lines):
{% for line in script.dialogue %}
{{ line.speaker }}: {{ line.text }}
{% endfor %}

### EVALUATION CRITERIA (score each 0–10, then average):
1. **News Coverage** (0–10): Does the dialogue accurately cover all {{ articles | length }} provided articles? Are the summaries faithful to the originals?
2. **Dialogue Quality** (0–10): Is the conversation natural, engaging, and does it reflect Alex (analytical) and Sam (enthusiastic technical) personalities correctly?
3. **TTS Readiness** (0–10): Is the text free of Markdown, symbols, stage directions, or any element that would sound unnatural when read aloud?
4. **Duration Estimate** (0–10): Is the estimated_duration ({{ script.estimated_duration }}s) plausible for the amount of dialogue? (~130 words ≈ 60 seconds)

### OUTPUT FORMAT:
Return ONLY a valid JSON object matching this exact schema — no extra text:
{
  "score": <float 0.0–10.0, average of the 4 criteria>,
  "justification": "<2–3 sentences summarizing overall quality and main strengths>",
  "needs_rewrite": <true if score < 6.0, otherwise false>,
  "feedback": "<specific actionable instructions for improvement, or null if needs_rewrite is false>"
}
